SENATE BILL 810
F1, E4 6lr2220
CF 6lr1751
By: Senator King
Introduced and read first time: February 6, 2026
Assigned to: Education, Energy, and the Environment and Judicial Proceedings
A BILL ENTITLED
1 AN ACT concerning
2 Public Schools – School Security Personnel – Immigration Investigation and
3 Enforcement
4 FOR the purpose of prohibiting public school security personnel from engaging in certain
5 federal immigration investigation and enforcement functions; prohibiting public
6 school security personnel from producing or sharing certain student or employee
7 information for purposes of federal immigration investigation and enforcement,
8 except under certain circumstances; and generally relating to federal immigration
9 investigation and enforcement in public schools.
10 BY repealing and reenacting, without amendments,
11 Article – Education
12 Section 7–1501(a), (j), and (k)
13 Annotated Code of Maryland
14 (2025 Replacement Volume and 2025 Supplement)
15 BY adding to
16 Article – Education
17 Section 7–1508.1
18 Annotated Code of Maryland
19 (2025 Replacement Volume and 2025 Supplement)
20 SECTION 1. BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF MARYLAND,
21 That the Laws of Maryland read as follows:
22 Article – Education
23 7–1501.
24 (a) In this subtitle the following words have the meanings indicated.
EXPLANATION: CAPITALS INDICATE MATTER ADDED TO EXISTING LAW.
[Brackets] indicate matter deleted from exist in g l aw . *sb0810*

2 SENATE BILL 810
1 (j) “School resource officer” means:
2 (1) A law enforcement officer as defined under § 1–101(c) of the Public
3 Safety Article who has been assigned to a school in accordance with a memorandum of
4 understanding between the chief of a law enforcement agency as defined under § 3–201(d)
5 of the Public Safety Article and the local education agency; or
6 (2) A Baltimore City school police officer, as defined in § 4–318 of this
7 article.
8 (k) “School security employee” means an individual, as defined in regulations
9 adopted by the Subcabinet, who:
10 (1) Is not a school resource officer; and
11 (2) Is employed by a local school system to provide safety and
12 security–related services at a public school.
13 7–1508.1.
14 (A) IN THIS SECTION, “PUBLIC SCHOOL SECURITY PERSONNEL” MEANS:
15 (1) A SCHOOL RESOURCE OFFICER, AS DEFINED IN § 7–1501 OF THIS
16 SUBTITLE;
17 (2) A SCHOOL SECURITY EMPLOYEE, AS DEFINED IN § 7–1501 OF THIS
18 SUBTITLE; OR
19 (3) A LAW ENFORCEMENT OFFICER WHO:
20 (I) IS NOT DIRECTLY ASSIGNED TO OR EMPLOYED BY A PUBLIC
21 SCHOOL;
22 (II) HAS NOT COMPLETED THE CENTER’S SCHOOL RESOURCE
23 OFFICER AND SCHOOL SECURITY EMPLOYEE TRAINING ACADEMY; AND
24 (III) PROVIDES ADEQUATE LAW ENFORCEMENT COVERAGE TO
25 PUBLIC SCHOOLS IN ACCORDANCE WITH AN AGREEMENT BETWEEN THE LOCAL LAW
26 ENFORCEMENT AGENCY AND THE LOCAL SCHOOL SYSTEM.
27 (B) PUBLIC SCHOOL SECURITY PERSONNEL MAY NOT:
28 (1) BE USED FOR PURPOSES OF OR OTHERWISE ENGAGE IN FEDERAL
29 IMMIGRATION INVESTIGATION OR ENFORCEMENT FUNCTIONS UNDER § 287(G) OF
30 THE FEDERAL IMMIGRATION AND NATIONALITY ACT AT THE PUBLIC SCHOOL; OR

SENATE BILL 810 3
1 (2) EXCEPT AS PROVIDED IN SUBSECTION (C) OF THIS SECTION,
2 PRODUCE OR SHARE INFORMATION OR A DOCUMENT PERTAINING TO STUDENT
3 EDUCATIONAL RECORDS OR EMPLOYEE PERSONNEL RECORDS OR ANY OTHER
4 INFORMATION ABOUT OR FROM A STUDENT, A PUBLIC SCHOOL EMPLOYEE, OR A
5 STUDENT’S OR A PUBLIC SCHOOL EMPLOYEE’S FAMILY OR HOUSEHOLD FOR
6 PURPOSES OF FEDERAL IMMIGRATION INVESTIGATION OR ENFORCEMENT.
7 (C) PUBLIC SCHOOL SECURITY PERSONNEL SHALL IMMEDIATELY CONTACT
8 THE COUNTY SUPERINTENDENT AND LEGAL COUNSEL FOR THE LOCAL SCHOOL
9 SYSTEM IF PRESENTED WITH A VALID:
10 (1) JUDICIAL WARRANT;
11 (2) JUDICIAL SUBPOENA; OR
12 (3) A LEGAL ORDER FOR THE PRODUCTION OF INFORMATION OR A
13 DOCUMENT REGARDING THE INDIVIDUALS DESCRIBED UNDER SUBSECTION (B)(2)
14 OF THIS SECTION.
15 (D) THIS SECTION SHALL BE CONSTRUED CONSISTENTLY WITH ANY
16 APPLICABLE FEDERAL AND STATE PRIVACY LAWS.
17 SECTION 2. AND BE IT FURTHER ENACTED, That this Act shall take effect July
18 1, 2026.

